cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a fixpoint characterization of winning sets and strategies in games played on an infinite probabilistic arena. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses games with objectives and winning strategies. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a possible category as the paper deals with decision problems and the decidability of games. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) could be another possible category as the paper discusses strategies and winning sets. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a possible category as the paper deals with probabilistic systems and their analysis.
